social_posts.post_text: Touring with kids is a grand adventure! 🥰🎄🎉 🚌

It’s been a while since I’ve done this, but there are some new faces around here, so it seemed as good a time as any! ✨

I’m Francesca, and I write and record Christian music. My husband manages my career and our homestead, is in seminary, and is a very involved father and disciple-maker. He also disciples men through a workout ministry in our small town. 

We have 6 beautiful blessings: Eli, Audrey, Isaac, Wyatt, Benjamin, and Annabeth. Four of them were birthed at home, and we are all about the natural lifestyle. We homeschool, and we try to live a quiet, slow, and intentional life. Too many activities makes me itchy. 🤪

We live on some land in Tennessee and have a zillion chickens, Muscovy ducks, bees, and barn cats a plenty. My heart is READY for a milk cow, but my mind knows we’re not quite there yet. We also have a beautiful garden oasis space thanks to the lovely @thedirtacademy! 🌱🐓 

We love Jesus and the church, and He has brought us into such beautiful community with our recent move to a small town. Bartering, supporting local farmers, and passing on the fruits of our labor is our jam. I can’t wait to see how our homestead grows!

Our home is small and humble, and we’d love to make it a little more comfortable for hosting in the years to come (and I’d love more than 3 kitchen cabinets 😂), but for now we love the closeness. 

Ok, I know I’m missing some things, but this is what I can think of for now! Tell me a little about you, and thank you for being here! 🥰

Don’t want to forget what a lovely Christmas we had this year, so consider this my scrapbook! We had an impromptu candlelight service at our home on Christmas Eve and a sweet time at church the next morning and opening presents with my folks. We ate tons of delicious food and celebrated Jesus with all we did. I feel so grateful. I’ll probably make another reel for our time in GA because it was super special all in its own way! ♥️
Georgia Christmas was a special time with family! We ate delicious food, played, laughed, and rested. Such a blessing! 🙌🏻 (Thank you for indulging my virtual scrapbook, friends!)

Who’s excited for growing season?! ☀️ As many of you know, our family has been working on our homestead for 2 years. Last spring we added a new garden space (swipe to see her!), and I’m so thankful we were able to connect with a like-minded company during that time called @agrigrohome. We have been using 2 of their products with amazing results, & we are offering you guys a discount code! The best part is that 100% of the proceeds will be given to 2 ministries that we love for this entire week (Mar 5-14)! 

@illuminationsbible is an alliance of 11 Bible translation partners who are reducing Bible poverty for the 1 billion people on earth without scripture in their language. Over 3000 languages have yet to be translated, and illumiNations plans to change that by 2033! Before these ministries came together, the date was 2150. 😮

The other wonderful ministry we get to support is @windriverranch! This beautiful horse ranch in the Rockies is a haven for families, veterans, and young people who long to be discipled in their faith, refreshed, and reconnected to creation. Our family was blessed to get to lead worship at the ranch last June, and it was truly the trip of a lifetime. Hearing the hearts of the staff and learning that they scholarship 50% of the guests moved us. My kids are busting to go back!

This poem made me cry. 
(Totally stole this idea from my girl @under_the_sassafras ♥️)

This old house. 
These quiet halls. 
These empty rooms, 
whisper from the past.

The walls lined with memories, 
still echoing their stories. 
Stories of hope and joy, 
grief and sorrow. 
The evidence of a life once 
lived together.

This kitchen table, 
once covered in crumbs 
and clamoring with life, 
now set for only two. 

Childhood slips away 
like the turn of autumn. 
Late-night feedings 
become late-night talks. 
Milk-drunk sleeps 
and baby’s breath – gone too soon.

Blessed are we, 
the ones who get to experience 
our children’s exhausted cries and desperate hugs. 
Their skinned knees 
and hidden peas and all. 

We long for it to stay 
like this forever. 
But children grow up, 
that’s what they do.

Eventually, they go off 
to create a life of their own. 
Maybe they’ll take the path we showed them. 
Maybe they’ll forge their own. 

One day, it will be 
their homes we visit. 
Holding their babes 
with raw and tender love.

We’ll remember how these long days made for short years. 
We’ll remember the time when they were ours, and we were theirs.
- @ainsl3y Ainsley Arment

The ones who show up faithfully day after day, pouring into their families, discipling their children, leading family worship, working hard to protect and provide, doing the unseen work of loving and leading day after day. It doesn’t have to be Father’s Day to say thank you. We need strong husbands and fathers who love the Lord, and we honor them.

🎄Merry Christmas from the Goodwins…and an announcement!!! 🎉 (Keep reading!) 2023 was such a special year for our family. We welcomed two new pups to our farm, had another great year in the garden, and Matt graduated from Liberty University with his Masters in theological studies! 👨🏻‍🎓 We’ve been blessed to continue homeschooling, Eli joined a basketball team, Audrey continued with ballet, and the little boys continue to have a lot of fun wherever they go! Annabeth has us all wrapped around her finger, and our favorite thing she says right now is, “Otay?!” 

She is excited as can be to tell you that, Lord willing, in June of 2024, she will graduate to the title of BIG SISTER!!! Yes, we are so excited to welcome baby number SEVEN to our brood! ♥️🙌🏻 The Lord has seen fit to bless us with more children, and we couldn’t be more thankful!!!

Praying you have a lovely and blessed Christmas and a happy New Year! 🎄🎉
